replies.body:
Hey man, sometimes it's a good strat. The Heart may be the strongest muscle, but Braum literally punches through mountains, so beefing up his biceps is a close second. 

Besides, you don't just go full attack speed, you just get Wit's End and Guinsoo's, everything else is tank + Titanic. Once you get Guinsoo's up and full Wit's End stacks you can stun people in like, Q + 2 autos with no help required. ~~I'm not memeing I swear~~
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}

Man, if only there was a champion who, in the mid and late game, could lock him down for the majority of his ult and then set up the kill for when it ends. 

It'd be a shame if they were to remove that design because it "limits design space" or some nebulous bullshit like that.
